21/02/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Albanians represent the largest number of legal immigrants in Greece, forming a total of 63.3 per cent of all foreign residents, according to a report of the Immigration Policy Institute released Sunday (20 February).
Bulgarians are second with 9.8 per cent, while Romanians are third with 4.3 per cent.
The report says the number of foreign nationals residing in Greece has increased over fourfold since 1991.
(ANA - 20/02/05)
